## PYTHON SCRIPTS (Office generation)

Location: `imagen_institucional_targetmaps/scripts/`

Install: `pip install python-docx python-pptx openpyxl`

| File        | Library      | Purpose                                              |
|-------------|--------------|------------------------------------------------------|
| tm_brand.py | stdlib only  | Brand constants: COLORS, FONTS, SIZES, CONTACT, LOGOS, TEXTOS |
| tm_docx.py  | python-docx  | DOCX helpers: cover, headings, tables, callouts, footer |
| tm_pptx.py  | python-pptx  | PPTX helpers: cover/content/closing slides, tables, KPI tiles |
| tm_xlsx.py  | openpyxl     | XLSX helpers: branded tables, KPI rows, titles, footers |

### DOCX — Key functions

```python
from tm_docx import (
    setup_document,      # Set margins and base font
    add_cover,           # Cover page
    add_heading1,        # H1: UPPERCASE, blue_dark, underline blue_mid
    add_heading2,        # H2: blue_mid, bold
    add_body_text,       # 10pt body paragraph
    add_bullet,          # Bullet with optional bold prefix
    add_caption,         # 8pt gray italic footnote
    add_table,           # Full branded table (header + alternating rows + optional total)
    add_kv_table,        # Key-value 2-column table
    add_callout,         # Dark blue callout box
    add_strength_card,   # Left-border highlight card
    add_formula_box,     # Monospace formula block
    add_contact_footer,  # Standard 3-line contact block
    add_confidentiality_block,
    build_propuesta,     # High-level: complete proposal in one call
)
```

### PPTX — Key functions

```python
from tm_pptx import (
    create_presentation,    # 16:9 blank presentation
    add_cover_slide,        # Dark blue cover: logo white, title, subtitle, client
    add_content_slide,      # White slide: blue top bar, title
    add_section_divider,    # Blue mid full-slide section break
    add_closing_slide,      # Dark blue closing: logo, contacts
    add_table_slide,        # Insert branded table into a slide
    add_kpi_tile,           # KPI tile: stripe bg, blue left border, label/value/delta
    add_text_box,           # Generic text box
    add_rect,               # Colored rectangle
    add_logo,               # Logo image (path-based)
)
```

### XLSX — Key functions

```python
from tm_xlsx import (
    setup_workbook,         # Workbook with TargetMaps metadata
    add_branded_table,      # Full table: header + alternating + subtotal + total rows
    add_sheet_title,        # Title + subtitle at top of sheet
    add_kpi_row,            # Row of KPI tiles (label / value / delta)
    style_header_cell,      # Single header cell
    style_data_cell,        # Single data cell (even/odd aware)
    style_total_cell,       # Single total row cell (#273371)
    style_subtotal_cell,    # Single subtotal cell (#D5E2F4)
    add_footer_row,         # Source + confidentiality + IGV note
    build_report_workbook,  # High-level: 3-sheet report (E1/E2/E3)
    save_workbook,          # Save with .xlsx enforcement
)
```

### Usage examples

**Complete proposal DOCX:**
```python
from tm_docx import build_propuesta
from tm_brand import get_acerca_de

doc = build_propuesta({
    "tipo_doc":      "PROPUESTA TÉCNICO-ECONÓMICA",
    "titulo":        "Data Enrichment para WIN Internet",
    "subtitulo":     "Enriquecimiento de base de suscriptores",
    "cliente":       "WIN Internet · César Atalaya",
    "numero":        "WIN2026v1",
    "elaborado_por": "Fernando Horna · Socio-Director · TargetMaps",
    "fecha":         "Junio 2026",
    "resumen_ejecutivo": "Este documento presenta...",
    "urgencia":      "El mercado avanza — cada mes sin datos precisos es posición perdida.",
    "antecedentes":  "WIN despliega fibra en zonas urbanas...",
    "objetivos":     ["Enriquecer base con hogares verticales", "Proyectar 2025-2031"],
    "entregables":   [{"item": "E1", "descripcion": "Hogares por departamento", "fecha_est": "5 días"}],
    "precios":       [{"nro": 1, "descripcion": "Data Enrichment Lima", "precio": 5000}],
    "proximos_pasos":["Aprobar propuesta", "Enviar base de datos", "Iniciar procesamiento"],
    "por_que_targetmaps": [
        ("Inventario propio de edificios", "Más de 15,000 edificios georreferenciados 2017-2025."),
        ("Única fuente sin datos de terceros", "Producción propia — no revendemos datos."),
    ],
    "acerca_de": get_acerca_de("telecomunicaciones"),
})
doc.save("WIN2026v1_propuesta.docx")
```

**Presentation PPTX:**
```python
from tm_pptx import create_presentation, add_cover_slide, add_content_slide, add_kpi_tile, add_closing_slide

prs = create_presentation()
add_cover_slide(prs, titulo="Geo Analytics para WIN", subtitulo="Proyección Hogares 2025-2031",
                cliente="WIN Internet", fecha="Junio 2026")
slide = add_content_slide(prs, titulo="Cifras Clave del Modelo")
add_kpi_tile(slide, "Hogares verticales nacionales", "1,336,433", "→ 1,781,637 en 2031 · +33.3%", left=0.5, top=2.0)
add_kpi_tile(slide, "% vertical Lima",               "30.3% → 34.1%", "+3.8 pp (2025-2031)",        left=4.6, top=2.0)
add_kpi_tile(slide, "Pisada WIN — verticales",       "1,263,478", "→ 1,693,497 en 2031",            left=8.7, top=2.0)
add_closing_slide(prs)
prs.save("WIN2026_presentacion.pptx")
```

